igher portion of parama=\r\ntma. Very rarely avataras descend entirely from paramatma without ANY jivat=\r\nma portion. Rama and Krishna are specific examples given by Parasara.\n&gt; =A0=\r\n\n&gt; They are entirely divine, but they do not encapsulate the entire divinit=\r\ny!!!! After all,\n&gt;  &quot;entire divinity&quot; cannot be encapsulated by any form ju=\r\nst as no cloud can contain the entire sky. They take part in the drama obey=\r\ning and executing the divine will but NOT altering it. This applies to Kris=\r\nhna as well as Rama.\n&gt; =A0\n&gt; *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 =\r\n*\n&gt; =A0\n&gt; &gt; Buddha was great spiritual force in this world. But I do not\n&gt; =\r\n&gt; see him fit in the scheme of evolutionary Avatars. His\n&gt; &gt; realization, t=\r\nhe one he advocated, is a static realization,\n&gt; &gt; an end in a void.\n&gt; =A0\n&gt;=\r\n First, he IS mentioned in SB list of avataras as well as Parasara&#39;s list. =\r\nIf he does not &quot;fit&quot; in your &quot;scheme of evolutionary Avatars&quot;, then your co=\r\nncept is possibly wrong and avataras are perhaps not &quot;evolutionary&quot; as you =\r\ntheorize.\n&gt; =A0\n&gt; Secondly, as per Parasara,\n&gt;  Buddha corresponds to Mercu=\r\nry, who personifies logical mind and the spirit of investigation and compre=\r\nhension. Logical mind and its spirit of comprehension are inherently fallib=\r\nle. Even a perfected spirit of comprehension is not capable of grasping the=\r\n Absolute Reality completely, for it is beyond comprehension. So, no wonder=\r\n it simplifies the Incomprehensible in an attempt to comprehend! That is wh=\r\nat Buddha ended up doing. However, logical mind has a great appeal in the A=\r\nge of Reason in this Kali yuga. No wonder Buddha was/is/will be a great spi=\r\nritual force in this world in this age.\n&gt; =A0\n&gt; *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt; =A0\n&gt; If you dismiss Parasara&#39;s linking of planets t=